    "body": "@obrakmann thanks for te review!\n\nThat's a mistake, that must be false (I was trying if it would still work, and it did). I added the parameter animation method to be able to execute the next activity right away just as with QueueActivity. \n\nIn this change I prevented an AttackBase activity to be scheduled if the actor is disabled. This will fix https://github.com/OpenRA/OpenRA/issues/7442 but I was still worried that maybe some other activity would jump in between the sell-animation and the actually sell. So I added the option to the QueueActivty and Render.\n"
